This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with the problem of detecting event-related queries, which is a common information retrieval task. Additionally, the paper proposes a deep learning model to classify queries into multiple event types, which falls under the sub-categories of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
